{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857798109,"sessionID":"ses_286a0b7b1ffeZtP3HSnErl6gaU","part":{"id":"prt_d795f87e6001KZPKIf53tBju24","messageID":"msg_d795f792d0016gqAKWwjWOb9xO","sessionID":"ses_286a0b7b1ffeZtP3HSnErl6gaU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-87fa2289baef4577a10f9cbb3dae81dd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: 实现 Redis 存储后端，包括:\n16: - `RedisSessionStore` 结构实现 SessionStore 接口\n17: - Redis 配置管理\n18: - Session 序列化/反序列化\n19: - 错误处理\n20: \n21: ## Out of Scope\n22: \n23: - Redis 集群支持\n24: - 分布式锁\n25: - 缓存预热\n26: - 数据迁移\n27: \n28: ## Dependencies\n29: \n30: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n31: |------------|---------|---------|\n32: | AR-012 | - | SessionStore 接口定义 |\n33: | go-redis/v9 | v9.x | Redis 客户端 |\n34: \n35: ## Deliverables\n36: \n37: | File | Description |\n38: |------|-------------|\n39: | `pkg/store/redis.go` | RedisSessionStore 实现 |\n40: | `pkg/store/redis_config.go` | Redis 配置结构 |\n41: | `pkg/store/redis_test.go` | 单元测试 |\n42: \n43: ## Acceptance Criteria\n44: \n45: - [ ] 实现完整的 SessionStore 接口\n46: - [ ] 支持配置化连接参数\n47: - [ ] 处理所有错误情况\n48: - [ ] 通过 `go vet` 和 `golangci-lint`\n49: - [ ] 单元测试覆盖率 ≥ 80%\n50: \n51: ## References\n52: \n53: - AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n(End of file - total 53 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n实现 Redis 存储后端，包括:\n- `RedisSessionStore` 结构实现 SessionStore 接口\n- Redis 配置管理\n- Session 序列化/反序列化\n- 错误处理\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/spec.md","time":{"start":1775857798088,"end":1775857798107}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857798112,"sessionID":"ses_286a0b7b1ffeZtP3HSnErl6gaU","part":{"id":"prt_d795f8bab001fIHo5FHT7j5gtd","messageID":"msg_d795f792d0016gqAKWwjWOb9xO","sessionID":"ses_286a0b7b1ffeZtP3HSnErl6gaU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-75be55a7ce794da289c09279b395e7c0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/store` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 实现 Redis/Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n14: \n15: ## Architecture\n16: \n17: ```\n18: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n19: │                      Application Layer                       │\n20: │                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │\n21: └────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n22:                                  │\n23:                                  v\n24: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                    Store Interface                            │\n26: │  Ping / GetSandboxBySessionID / StoreSandbox / UpdateSandbox│\n27: │  DeleteSandboxBySessionID / ListExpiredSandboxes            │\n28: │  ListInactiveSandboxes / UpdateSessionLastActivity / Close   │\n29: └────────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┘\n30:                                  │\n31:               ┌──────────────────┴──────────────────┐\n32:               v                                     v\n33: ┌─────────────────────────┐           ┌─────────────────────────┐\n34: │     redisStore          │           │     valkeyStore         │\n35: │ (go-redis/v9 Client)    │           │ (valkey-go Client)      │\n36: └───────────┬─────────────┘           └───────────┬─────────────┘\n37:             v                                     v\n38: ┌─────────────────────────┐           ┌─────────────────────────┐\n39: │      Redis Server       │           │     Valkey Server       │\n40: │   (Single/Cluster)      │           │   (Single/Cluster)      │\n41: └─────────────────────────┘           └─────────────────────────┘\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ### Provider Selection\n45: \n46: ```\n47:                     ┌─────────────────┐\n48:                     │   Storage()     │\n49:                     │  (singleton)    │\n50:                     └────────┬────────┘\n51:                              │ initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n52:                              v\n53:                     ┌─────────────────┐\n54:                     │  STORE_TYPE?    │\n55:                     └────────┬────────┘\n56:                              │\n57:               ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐\n58:               v              v              v\n59:         \"redis\"         \"valkey\"        other/empty\n60:               │              │              │\n61:               v              v              v\n62:       ┌───────────┐  ┌───────────┐  ┌───────────────┐\n63:       │redisStore │  │valkeyStore│  │Error: invalid│\n64:       └───────────┘  └───────────┘  │  provider     │\n65:                                     └───────────────┘\n66: ```\n67: \n68: ## Data Structures\n69: \n70: ### Store Interface\n71: \n72: ```go\n73: package store\n74: \n75: import (\n76:     \"context\"\n77:     \"time\"\n78: \n79:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n80: )\n81: \n82: type Store interface {\n83:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n84:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n85:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n86:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n87:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n88:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n89:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n90:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n91:     Close() error\n92: }\n93: ```\n94: \n95: ### Errors\n96: \n97: ```go\n98: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Provider Type Constants\n102: \n103: ```go\n104: const (\n105:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n106:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n107: )\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Redis Implementation\n111: \n112: ```go\n113: type redisStore struct {\n114:     cli                  *redisv9.Client\n115:     sessionPrefix        string\n116:     expiryIndexKey       string\n117:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n118: }\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Valkey Implementation\n122: \n123: ```go\n124: type valkeyStore struct {\n125:     cli                  valkey.Client\n126:     sessionPrefix        string\n127:     expiryIndexKey       string\n128:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n129: }\n130: ```\n131: \n132: ### Singleton\n133: \n134: ```go\n135: var (\n136:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n137:     provider      Store\n138: )\n139: \n140: func Storage() Store {\n141:     initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)\n142:     return provider\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ## Redis Key Design\n147: \n148: | Key Pattern | Type | Purpose |\n149: |-------------|------|---------|\n150: | `session:{id}` | String | JSON document storing SandboxInfo |\n151: | `session:expiry` | ZSET | Index of sessions by expiry timestamp (score = ExpiresAt Unix) |\n152: | `session:last_activity` | ZSET | Index of sessions by last activity (score = Unix timestamp) |\n153: \n154: ### Key Construction\n155: \n156: ```go\n157: func sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n158:     return sessionPrefix + sessionID  // \"session:\" + id\n159: }\n160: ```\n161: \n162: ### Document Structure\n163: \n164: ```\n165: session:abc123 = {\n166:   \"kind\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n167:   \"sandboxId\": \"sb-456\",\n168:   \"sandboxNamespace\": \"default\",\n169:   \"sandboxName\": \"my-sandbox\",\n170:   \"name\": \"session-name\",\n171:   \"sessionId\": \"abc123\",\n172:   \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\",\n173:   \"expiresAt\": \"2024-01-02T00:00:00Z\",\n174:   \"status\": \"active\",\n175:   \"entryPoints\": [...],\n176:   \"userToken\": \"...\",\n177:   \"serviceAccount\": \"...\",\n178:   \"serviceAccountName\": \"...\"\n179: }\n180: ```\n181: \n182: ## API Contracts\n183: \n184: ### Ping\n185: \n186: ```go\n187: func (s *redisStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n188: func (s *valkeyStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n189: ```\n190: \n191: - Redis: `PING` command, expects `PONG` response\n192: - Valkey: `B().Ping().Build()`, expects `PONG` string\n193: \n194: ### GetSandboxBySessionID\n195: \n196: ```go\n197: func (s *redisStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n198: func (s *valkeyStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n199: ```\n200: \n201: - Redis: `GET session:{id}`, `redis.Nil` → `ErrNotFound`\n202: - Valkey: `B().Get().Key(key).Build()`, `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound`\n203: \n204: ### StoreSandbox\n205: \n206: ```go\n207: func (s *redisStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n208: func (s *valkeyStore) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n209: ```\n210: \n211: **Validation:**\n212: - Reject nil sandbox\n213: - Reject zero ExpiresAt\n214: \n215: **Atomic Operations (Pipeline/Multi):**\n216: 1. `SETNX session:{id} <json>` - Only create if not exists\n217: 2. `ZADD session:expiry {expiresAtUnix} {sessionID}` - Add to expiry index\n218: 3. `ZADD session:last_activity {nowUnix} {sessionID}` - Add to activity index\n219: \n220: **Returns:** Error if any command fails or session already exists\n221: \n222: ### UpdateSandbox\n223: \n224: ```go\n225: func (s *redisStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n226: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n227: ```\n228: \n229: - Redis: `SET session:{id} <json> XX` (XX = only if exists)\n230: - Valkey: `B().Set().Key(key).Value(json).Build()` with existence check\n231: - Does NOT modify expiry or last_activity ZSETs\n232: - Returns error if key doesn't exist\n233: \n234: ### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n235: \n236: ```go\n237: func (s *redisStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n238: func (s *valkeyStore) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n239: ```\n240: \n241: **Atomic Operations (Pipeline/Multi):**\n242: 1. `DEL session:{id}`\n243: 2. `ZREM session:expiry {sessionID}`\n244: 3. `ZREM session:last_activity {sessionID}`\n245: \n246: ### ListExpiredSandboxes\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: func (s *redisStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n250: func (s *valkeyStore) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n251: ```\n252: \n253: - If `limit <= 0`, returns `nil, nil`\n254: - `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n255: - Pipeline GET for each session ID\n256: - Skips missing keys (orphan ZSET members)\n257: \n258: ### ListInactiveSandboxes\n259: \n260: ```go\n261: func (s *redisStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n262: func (s *valkeyStore) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n263: ```\n264: \n265: - Same logic as ListExpiredSandboxes but uses `session:last_activity` ZSET\n266: - `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix()} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n267: \n268: ### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n269: \n270: ```go\n271: func (s *redisStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n272: func (s *valkeyStore) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n273: ```\n274: \n275: **Validation:**\n276: - Reject empty sessionID\n277: - If `at` is zero, use `time.Now()`\n278: \n279: **Operations:**\n280: 1. Check if `session:{id}` exists\n281: 2. If not exists, return `ErrNotFound`\n282: 3. `ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {sessionID}`\n283: \n284: ### Close\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: func (s *redisStore) Close() error\n288: func (s *valkeyStore) Close() error\n289: ```\n290: \n291: - Close the underlying client connection\n292: \n293: ## Error Handling\n294: \n295: ### Custom Errors\n296: \n297: ```go\n298: var (\n299:     ErrNotFound              = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n300:     ErrNilSandbox           = errors.New(\"store: sandbox is nil\")\n301:     ErrZeroExpiresAt        = errors.New(\"store: expiresAt is required\")\n302:     ErrEmptySessionID       = errors.New(\"store: sessionID is required\")\n303:     ErrInvalidProvider      = errors.New(\"store: invalid provider type\")\n304:     ErrPasswordRequired     = errors.New(\"store: password is required\")\n305:     ErrKeyNotExists        = errors.New(\"store: key not exists\")\n306: )\n307: ```\n308: \n309: ### Error Wrapping Examples\n310: \n311: ```go\n312: // Redis\n313: if err == redis.Nil {\n314:     return ErrNotFound\n315: }\n316: return fmt.Errorf(\"store: get session %s: %w\", sessionID, err)\n317: \n318: // Valkey\n319: if valkey.IsValkeyNil(resp) {\n320:     return nil, ErrNotFound\n321: }\n322: ```\n323: \n324: ## Configuration\n325: \n326: ### Environment Variables (Redis)\n327: \n328: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n329: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n330: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Provider type (`redis` or `valkey`) |\n331: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis address (e.g., `localhost:6379`) |\n332: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Password (required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`) |\n333: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n334: \n335: ### Environment Variables (Valkey)\n336: \n337: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n338: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n339: | `STORE_TYPE` | Yes | - | Must be `valkey` |\n340: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated addresses |\n341: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Password (required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`) |\n342: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to disable password requirement |\n343: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to disable client-side cache |\n344: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | Set to `true` to force single client mode |\n345: \n346: ### Connection Options\n347: \n348: ```go\n349: // Redis\n350: func makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error) {\n351:     addr := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_ADDR\")\n352:     if addr == \"\" {\n353:         return nil, errors.New(\"REDIS_ADDR is required\")\n354:     }\n355:     \n356:     password := os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD\")\n357:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n358:     if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n359:         return nil, ErrPasswordRequired\n360:     }\n361:     \n362:     return &redisv9.Options{\n363:         Addr:     addr,\n364:         Password: password,\n365:     }, nil\n366: }\n367: \n368: // Valkey\n369: func makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error) {\n370:     addr := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_ADDR\")\n371:     if addr == \"\" {\n372:         return nil, errors.New(\"VALKEY_ADDR is required\")\n373:     }\n374:     \n375:     password := os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD\")\n376:     passwordRequired := strings.ToLower(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\"))\n377:     if password == \"\" && passwordRequired != \"false\" {\n378:         return nil, ErrPasswordRequired\n379:     }\n380:     \n381:     opts := &valkey.ClientOption{\n382:         InitAddress: strings.Split(addr, \",\"),\n383:         Password:    password,\n384:     }\n385:     \n386:     if v, _ := strconv.ParseBool(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE\")); v {\n387:         opts.DisableCache = true\n388:     }\n389:     if v, _ := strconv.ParseBool(os.Getenv(\"VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE\")); v {\n390:         opts.ForceSingleClient = true\n391:     }\n392:     \n393:     return opts, nil\n394: }\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ## Testing Strategy\n398: \n399: ### Unit Tests\n400: \n401: ```go\n402: // Using miniredis for Redis tests\n403: func TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n404:     s := miniredis.RunT(t)\n405:     store := NewRedisStore(s.Addr(), \"\")\n406:     \n407:     // Test successful store\n408:     // Test duplicate store (SETNX behavior)\n409:     // Test nil sandbox rejection\n410:     // Test zero ExpiresAt rejection\n411: }\n412: \n413: // Using mocked valkey client for Valkey tests\n414: func TestValkeyStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n415:     // Test with mock client\n416: }\n417: ```\n418: \n419: ### Test Categories\n420: \n421: | Test Category | Description |\n422: |--------------|-------------|\n423: | Ping | Connectivity verification |\n424: | GetSandboxBySessionID | Found / not found |\n425: | StoreSandbox | Create new, reject duplicate, validation |\n426: | UpdateSandbox | Update existing, reject missing |\n427: | DeleteSandboxBySessionID | Remove all keys and ZSET members |\n428: | ListExpiredSandboxes | Query by expiry ZSET, handle missing docs |\n429: | ListInactiveSandboxes | Query by activity ZSET, handle missing docs |\n430: | UpdateSessionLastActivity | Check existence, update ZSET score |\n431: | Close | Clean shutdown |\n432: \n433: ### Integration Tests\n434: \n435: ```go\n436: func TestRedisStore_Integration(t *testing.T) {\n437:     if testing.Short() {\n438:         t.Skip(\"skipping integration test\")\n439:     }\n440:     \n441:     // Use real Redis or miniredis\n442:     // Verify end-to-end operations\n443:     // Test pipeline atomicity\n444: }\n445: ```\n446: \n447: ### Test Utilities\n448: \n449: ```go\n450: func setupTestRedis(t *testing.T) *redisStore {\n451:     mr := miniredis.RunT(t)\n452:     return &redisStore{\n453:         cli:                  redisv9.NewClient(&redisv9.Options{Addr: mr.Addr()}),\n454:         sessionPrefix:        \"session:\",\n455:         expiryIndexKey:       \"session:expiry\",\n456:         lastActivityIndexKey: \"session:last_activity\",\n457:     }\n458: }\n459: \n460: func makeTestSandbox(sessionID string) *types.SandboxInfo {\n461:     return &types.SandboxInfo{\n462:         Kind:             types.AgentRuntimeKind,\n463:         SandboxID:        \"sb-\" + sessionID,\n464:         SandboxNamespace: \"default\",\n465:         Name:             \"test-sandbox\",\n466:         SessionID:         sessionID,\n467:         CreatedAt:        time.Now(),\n468:         ExpiresAt:        time.Now().Add(24 * time.Hour),\n469:         Status:           \"active\",\n470:     }\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ## File Structure\n475: \n476: ```\n477: pkg/store/\n478:   store.go           — Store interface, ErrNotFound, singleton access\n479:   store_redis.go    — redisStore implementation\n480:   store_valkey.go   — valkeyStore implementation\n481:   store_test.go     — Unit tests (using miniredis and mocks)\n482:   doc.go            — Package documentation\n483: ```\n484: \n485: ## Dependencies\n486: \n487: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n488: |---------|---------|---------|\n489: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | latest | Redis client |\n490: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | latest | Valkey client |\n491: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | latest | Logging |\n492: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | local | SandboxInfo type |\n493: \n494: ## Performance Considerations\n495: \n496: ### Redis Implementation\n497: \n498: 1. **Pipeline for Atomicity**: StoreSandbox and DeleteSandboxBySessionID use pipelines to ensure atomic multi-key operations\n499: 2. **MGET for Batch Reads**: ListExpiredSandboxes/ListInactiveSandboxes can batch GET requests\n500: 3. **Connection Pooling**: go-redis manages connection pooling automatically\n501: \n502: ### Valkey Implementation\n503: \n504: 1. **DoMulti for Atomicity**: Similar to Redis pipeline\n505: 2. **Mget for Batch Reads**: Single MGET command for multiple session documents\n506: 3. **Client-Side Cache**: Optional `DisableCache` for memory-sensitive deployments\n507: \n508: ### Key Locality\n509: \n510: For Valkey cluster deployments, ensure session keys and ZSET keys map to the same slot by using hash tags:\n511: \n512: ```\n513: session:{sessionID}          → uses hash tag\n514: session:expiry               → no hash tag needed (single key)\n515: session:last_activity        → no hash tag needed (single key)\n516: ```\n517: \n518: Note: Current implementation assumes single-node or properly sharded deployment. For multi-node clusters, consider using hash tags for session IDs.\n519: \n520: ## Security Considerations\n521: \n522: 1. **Password Protection**: Password required by default, can be disabled for local development\n523: 2. **TLS Support**: Both go-redis and valkey-go support TLS connections (add via config)\n524: 3. **No Secrets in Logs**: Ensure session data with UserToken is not logged\n525: \n526: ## Migration Notes\n527: \n528: If migrating from a previous store implementation:\n529: \n530: 1. Data migration script to convert existing sessions to new JSON format\n531: 2. Rebuild ZSET indexes from existing session data\n532: 3. Run dual-write period during migration window\n533: \n534: ## References\n535: \n536: - AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Store interface)\n537: - Redis Documentation: https://redis.io/docs/\n538: - go-redis Documentation: https://redis.uptrace.dev/\n539: - Valkey-go Documentation: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n\n(End of file - total 539 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-013 — Redis 存储实现 |\n| Module | `pkg/store` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n实现 Redis/Valkey 存储后端，提供高性能的会话持久化能力，支持按过期时间和最后活跃时间索引以便垃圾回收。\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Application Layer                       │\n│                    (Session Manager, GC)                      │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","time":{"start":1775857798092,"end":1775857798109}}}}
